"{\"uid\": \"gbnews.com-sport-other-sport-olympics-opening-ceremony-start-time-full-guide-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics opening ceremony will take place on the River Seine  GETTY  ByStuart Ballard,  Published: 26/07/2024  The 2024 Paris Olympics officially get underway this evening with thousands of athletes set to be involved in the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 59, \"end\": 70, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 88, \"end\": 95, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"score\": 0.8873758369794448, \"rank\": 0.12691818972402436, \"text\": \"Ballard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._G._Ballard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris will host an Olympics opening ceremony like no other this evening as the first to be held outside of a stadium.\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 254, \"end\": 259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997214672, \"rank\": 2.784883477462167e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be the largest opening ceremony in Olympics history with as many as 500,000 people expected to line the River Seine to watch the ceremony.\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 485, \"end\": 496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around 10,000 athletes will sail down the 6km stretch of the river on 85 barges and boats, starting from the Austerlitz bridge.Unlike previous opening ceremonies and due to the sheer size and complexity of the parade, there has been no full rehearsal.The Paris Olympics opening ceremony will take place on the River Seine|GETTYTheatre director Thomas Jolly is the architect of the show, which is set to be split into 12 different sections throughout the evening.Entertainers and dancers are set to be positioned on either side of the river as well as the bridges and nearby monuments along the route.GB Newsprovides a full guide on what to look out for and how to watch the Paris Olympics opening ceremony.Olympics opening ceremony start timeThe ceremony will begin at 7.30pm local time (6.30pm BST).It is expected to last up to four hours with Australia, USA and France the final boats to join the parade.How to watch the opening ceremonyThe opening ceremony will be shown live on BBC One throughout the evening with coverage starting at 5.45pm.Clare Balding will present the coverage on BBC with the likes of Laura Kenny, Jazmin Sawyers and Moe Sbihi among those set to feature on the channel throughout the Games.None of the opening ceremony will take place inside a stadium|GETTYThe coverage will also be available on Eurosport and Discovery+, although they require a subscription.Team GB flag bearersTom Daley and Helen Glover have been selected as Team GB's flag bearers for the Paris Olympics opening ceremony.Daley ended his long wait for an Olympic gold medal in Tokyo alongside Matty Lee while Glover is a two-time Olympic champion.LATEST SPORT NEWS:Andy Murray comments on Emma Raducanu controversy speak volumes ahead of Paris OlympicsGordon Ramsay says Team GB star is 'full of s**t' as question goes unanswered ahead of Paris OlympicsEngland suffer major next manager blow as dream candidate drops hint following Gareth Southgate resignationHelen Glover and Tom Daley will be the flagbearers for Team GB|GETTYThe Games in Paris will see Daley become the first British diver to compete in five Olympics having made his debut as a 14 year old back in 2008.Glover has come out of retirement twice and will competing in her fourth Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 2776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9922455929265561, \"rank\": 0.007625986321463187, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}, {\"begin\": 1366, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.7162089254113486, \"rank\": 0.3627850268184112, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1377, \"end\": 1380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.5675503390342644, \"rank\": 0.7096278477368809, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1385, \"end\": 1391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9119171161219968, \"rank\": 0.07951428225348474, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_One\", \"score\": 0.914717386436831, \"rank\": 0.08507789421913071, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_